
@startuml
skinparam noteStyle rectangle

class School {
  -name: String
  -principal: Teacher
  -rooms: Set<Room>
  -classGroups: Set<ClassGroup>
}

class Teacher {
  -firstName: String
  -lastName: String
  -email: String
  -schools: Set<School>
  -hoursTeaching: Map<School, Integer>
}

class Student {
  -firstName: String
  -lastName: String
  -school: School
  -classGroup: ClassGroup
}

class Room {
  -name: String
  -capacity: Integer
  -size: Integer
  -type: String
}

class ClassGroup {
  -name: String
  -students: Set<Student>
  -room: Room
}

School "1" -- "1" ClassGroup : has
ClassGroup "1" -- "1" Room : assigned to
Student "1" -- "1" ClassGroup : belongs to
ClassGroup "1" -- "1" School : belongs to
Teacher "1" -- "1" School : teaches at
School "1" -- "1" Teacher : principal
Teacher "1" -- "*" School : teaches at (max 3)
Teacher "1" -- "0..1" School : principal (only one)

@enduml

### Explanation of Relationships:

- **School** has a **principal**, who is a **Teacher**.
- A **Teacher** can be the **principal** of **one** school only.
- A **Teacher** can teach at **up to three** schools, and the number of hours per teaching relationship is tracked.
- A **Student** belongs to **exactly one** **ClassGroup**, and each **ClassGroup** has **exactly one** **Room**.
- A **Room** can be a **classroom** (with capacity) or another type of room (e.g., gym with size).
- Each **ClassGroup** has **between 10 and 31 students**.

